"content": "<p>Soldiers who offers their services for money, irrespective of the nationality of the army in question.</p>\n<h2>Mercenaries in the Egyptian army</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:20-Jer46:21\">JER 46:20–46:21</a></strong> <em>These mercenaries were drawn from Cush to the south of Egypt, Put to the west of Egypt and Lydia in north Africa.</em></p>\n<h2>Mercenaries in the Ammonite army</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam10:6\">2SA 10:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr19:7\">1CH 19:7</a></p>\n<h2>Mercenaries hired by Jehoiada the priest</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:4\">2KI 11:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:19\">2KI 11:19</a> <em>The Carites were from Caria in south-west Asia Minor.</em></p>\n<h2>Mercenaries in the army of Judah</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:6\">2CH 25:6</a></p>\n<h2>Fear of mercenary attack</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs7:6-2Kgs7:7\">2KI 7:6–7:7</a></p>",
